      <h2>Welcome to the heart of Provo’s Social Media Usage and Mental Health (SMU&MH) Committee!</h2>

      <p>Our passion resonates with understanding the delicate balance between the vibrant world of social media and our 
        mental well-being. Picture this: a digital landscape teeming with possibilities, but with an ethos centered
        around harnessing its power judiciously. Our mission is not just about unraveling the mysteries of social media; 
        it's about crafting a symphony of strategies that allow us to harmoniously navigate life's highs and lows amidst 
        the ever-present allure of our digital age.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Journey</h2>
      <p>Here at SMU&MH, we embark on a fascinating journey, where the goal isn't merely to avoid social media but to 
        embrace it thoughtfully. We aim to transform the way we engage online, to transform it into a catalyst for 
        building a vibrant and deeply connected community right here in Provo. It's not about disconnecting but about 
        connecting meaningfully, fostering genuine relationships, and using these digital platforms as tools for positive 
        change.
      </p>
      <br>
      <p>Together, let's craft a digital era where social media isn't just an endless void of doom scrolling but a canvas 
        for fostering empathy, supporting mental wellness, and forging meaningful connections. Let's explore these 
        platforms while cherishing the invaluable moments of human connection they enable.
      </p>

      <h2>Join Our Mission</h2>
      <p>Welcome to our mission – a journey not just to coexist with social media but to thrive alongside it, 
        sculpting a community in Provo where technology and humanity walk hand in hand, illuminating our path to a brighter, 
        healthier future.</p>

